WEBVTT

00:09.843 --> 00:11.179
- * ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR!

00:11.212 --> 00:12.780
* ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX! *

00:12.813 --> 00:13.781
* SHAKE IT, DUDE!

00:13.814 --> 00:21.755
*

00:32.300 --> 00:34.268
* ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR!

00:34.302 --> 00:37.505
*

00:41.575 --> 00:44.112
- * ONCE IS NOT ENOUGH,
I GOTTA DO IT ALL THE TIME *

00:44.145 --> 00:45.646
* GOTTA HAVE THIS FEELIN'

00:45.679 --> 00:46.680
* TILL I'M GOING BLIND

00:46.714 --> 00:50.318
- 950.

00:50.351 --> 00:52.153
- OOH, YEAH.

00:52.186 --> 00:53.287
[cash register dings]
- 975.

00:53.321 --> 00:54.355
- [moaning]

00:54.388 --> 00:55.389
- 980.

00:55.423 --> 00:56.424
985.

00:56.457 --> 00:57.825
- [growling]
- 990!

00:57.858 --> 00:59.427
- [groaning]

00:59.460 --> 01:00.761
- 995.

01:00.794 --> 01:02.263
997.
- [grunts]

01:02.296 --> 01:03.631
- 998.
- [grunts]

01:03.664 --> 01:05.566
- 1,000!
- [grunts]

01:05.599 --> 01:06.600
YEAH!

01:06.634 --> 01:07.768
UNH!

01:07.801 --> 01:11.472
- 1,003!
- [grunts]

01:11.505 --> 01:13.474
- YES, SIR!

01:13.507 --> 01:16.710
[chuckles]

01:16.744 --> 01:20.348
OVER 1,000 SELF-SATISFIED
CUSTOMERS.

01:20.381 --> 01:23.851
[chuckles]
AND WE'RE OUT.

01:23.884 --> 01:26.587
WHOO!

01:26.620 --> 01:30.724
- [panting]
- ALL RIGHT.

01:30.758 --> 01:32.160
- [groans]

01:32.193 --> 01:36.864
- YOU TAKE TEN,
AND THEN WE WILL START...

01:36.897 --> 01:38.199
ROUND THREE.

01:38.232 --> 01:40.134
- OH, NO CAN DO.

01:40.168 --> 01:42.870
HONEY, MY DICK'S
DOWN FOR THE COUNT.

01:42.903 --> 01:44.338
- LISTEN NOW,

01:44.372 --> 01:45.606
THERE ARE A LOT
OF FANS OUT THERE

01:45.639 --> 01:47.775
WHO ARE WANTING
TO SEE YOU GO FOR THE RECORD.

01:47.808 --> 01:49.143
- THE RECORD?

01:49.177 --> 01:52.680
- SET BY THE LEGENDARY
PETER POUNDER.

01:52.713 --> 01:58.319
- HE ONCE CAME SIX TIMES
IN 45 MINUTES.

01:58.352 --> 02:01.322
- SIX TIMES
IN 45 MINUTES?

02:01.355 --> 02:05.693
I HAVEN'T DONE THAT
SINCE I WAS 18.

02:05.726 --> 02:07.861
- WELL, THEN,
DON'T YOU WORRY

02:07.895 --> 02:09.830
YOUR PRETTY
LITTLE DICK ABOUT IT.

02:09.863 --> 02:13.901
TWICE IN 30 MINUTES
IS VERY...

02:13.934 --> 02:17.771
RESPECTABLE.

02:17.805 --> 02:19.840
- RESPECTABLE?

02:22.743 --> 02:24.345
REV UP THE WEB CAM,
BOYS.

02:24.378 --> 02:26.514
WE'RE GOING
FOR THE GOLD.

02:26.547 --> 02:28.616
[boxing bell rings]
- ATTA-BOY, CHAMP.

02:28.649 --> 02:32.386
- * IT'S FIVE AGAINST ONE,
NEVER SHOW YOUR HAND *

02:32.420 --> 02:33.887
- AND WE'RE LIVE.

02:33.921 --> 02:36.757
- * I'M A CLIMAX JUNKIE

02:36.790 --> 02:38.926
* CLIMAX JUNKIE

02:38.959 --> 02:41.595
* ONCE IS NOT ENOUGH
- OH, YEAH.

02:43.697 --> 02:44.698
[door closes]

02:44.732 --> 02:45.766
- I MADE YOU SAUSAGE
AND PEPPERS,

02:45.799 --> 02:47.668
AND I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
A GODDAMNED WORD ABOUT IT.

02:47.701 --> 02:49.270
- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

02:49.303 --> 02:51.272
IF IT WASN'T FOR YOU,
I'D PROBABLY STARVE TO DEATH.

02:51.305 --> 02:53.374
- WELL, AS THE MOTHER
OF A FUTURE CAPTAIN OF INDUSTRY,

02:53.407 --> 02:55.243
I COULDN'T VERY WELL
LET THAT HAPPEN.

02:55.276 --> 02:56.677
- WELL, I DON'T WANT
TO BURST YOUR BUBBLE, MOM,

02:56.710 --> 02:58.779
BUT I'M NOT EXACTLY
GONNA BECOME A GAZILLIONAIRE

02:58.812 --> 03:00.414
SELLING COMICS.

03:00.448 --> 03:02.283
- EVERYBODY HAS
TO START SOMEWHERE, SWEETHEART.

03:02.316 --> 03:05.286
AND YOU'VE STARTED,
THAT'S WHAT'S IMPORTANT.

03:05.319 --> 03:07.755
I'M SO PROUD
OF YOU, MICHAEL.

03:07.788 --> 03:10.291
YOU'VE TURNED OUT
TO BE QUITE A MAN.

03:10.324 --> 03:11.459
CHEW YOUR FOOD.

03:11.492 --> 03:15.496
[pop song
plays in background]

03:15.529 --> 03:17.498
- HEY.
- HEY.

03:17.531 --> 03:20.301
UH, I WAS
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

03:20.334 --> 03:22.603
UM, YOU LEFT THIS
AT MY PLACE.

03:24.638 --> 03:26.307
- HIS PLACE?

03:26.340 --> 03:28.542
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE GETTING LAID.

03:28.576 --> 03:31.345
GOOD FOR YOU.
[door opens]

03:31.379 --> 03:33.614
I'M HIS MOTHER.
- YES. I REMEMBER.

03:33.647 --> 03:35.549
- OH. HE REMEMBERS ME.

03:35.583 --> 03:37.318
- YOU'RE A LITTLE HARD
TO FORGET.

03:37.351 --> 03:39.320
AND FOR YOUR INFORMATION,
I DIDN'T GET LAID.

03:39.353 --> 03:42.556
- OH. TOO BAD.

03:42.590 --> 03:45.393
WELL...

03:45.426 --> 03:47.428
I HAVE TO GET BACK
TO THE DINER.

03:47.461 --> 03:50.531
IT'S NICE SEEING YOU AGAIN.

03:50.564 --> 03:51.899
BETTER LUCK THIS TIME.

03:51.932 --> 03:53.901
[chuckles]
BYE.

03:59.373 --> 04:00.808
- THAT IS SOME KIND
OF MOTHER YOU GOT THERE.

04:00.841 --> 04:02.610
- YOU DON'T KNOW THE HALF.

04:02.643 --> 04:04.878
- [chuckles]
YEAH. I'D LIKE TO.

04:04.912 --> 04:08.516
AND I'D LIKE TO KNOW
ALL THERE IS TO KNOW ABOUT YOU.

04:08.549 --> 04:09.883
- STOP,
YOU'RE MAKING ME BLUSH.

04:09.917 --> 04:11.519
WHICH, AFTER
GROWING UP WITH HER,

04:11.552 --> 04:12.986
YOU'D THINK WOULD BE IMPOSSIBLE.

04:13.020 --> 04:15.356
- YEAH. I ALSO WANTED
TO SEE HOW YOU WERE....

04:15.389 --> 04:18.025
UM, HOW YOU WERE DOING
AFTER LAST NIGHT.

04:18.058 --> 04:20.928
YOU KNOW, AFTER
MY BIG ANNOUNCEMENT.

04:20.961 --> 04:22.496
HI, THERE, MY NAME'S BEN.

04:22.530 --> 04:24.698
I'M 33. PISCES.
LOVE THE OUTDOORS.

04:24.732 --> 04:26.567
AND I'M HIV POSITIVE.

04:26.600 --> 04:28.536
YOU KNOW, IT'S, UH...

04:28.569 --> 04:29.703
I STILL HAVEN'T
FIGURED OUT A WAY

04:29.737 --> 04:32.840
TO DROP THAT BOMB GRACEFULLY.

04:32.873 --> 04:34.475
- I HOPE I DIDN'T
SEEM TOO THROWN.

04:34.508 --> 04:36.377
IT'S JUST THE FIRST TIME
IT'S COME UP WITH SOMEONE

04:36.410 --> 04:38.379
THAT I'VE BEEN INTERESTED IN.

04:38.412 --> 04:43.851
- INTERESTED AS IN--
AS IN STILL INTERESTED?

04:43.884 --> 04:46.354
WELL, THAT'S GOOD.

04:46.387 --> 04:49.523
SOME GUYS, YOU TELL THEM,
THEY RUN FOR THE DOOR.

04:49.557 --> 04:51.659
SO YOU'RE NOT--
YOU'RE NOT FREAKED OUT.

04:51.692 --> 04:53.694
- PLEASE. RIGHT AFTER
MY MOTHER TOLD ME I WAS GAY,

04:53.727 --> 04:55.829
SHE GAVE ME THIS BIG
SAFE SEX LECTURE.

04:55.863 --> 04:57.631
I--I KNEW HOW TO PUT
A CONDOM ON A CUCUMBER

04:57.665 --> 04:59.900
BEFORE I KNEW
HOW TO DRIVE.

04:59.933 --> 05:01.669
- YEAH, WELL--
YOU KNOW, I--

05:01.702 --> 05:03.504
I WAS GONNA
ASK YOU OUT TONIGHT,

05:03.537 --> 05:06.940
BUT NOW I'M NOT SO SURE.

05:06.974 --> 05:08.542
- WHY NOT?

05:08.576 --> 05:12.646
- WELL, MICHAEL, A CUCUMBER
IS A LOT TO LIVE UP TO.

05:12.680 --> 05:16.083
[laughter]

05:16.116 --> 05:18.819
- WHAT D'YA SAY, DOC?
SHE GONNA LIVE?

05:18.852 --> 05:21.121
- YOU GOT GRIEF
IN THE GEARBOX, BABY,

05:21.154 --> 05:22.690
JUST LIKE MY LOVE LIFE.

05:22.723 --> 05:24.592
- SO HOW MUCH
ARE WE LOOKING AT?

05:24.625 --> 05:26.394
- WELL, IT AIN'T
GONNA BE CHEAP.

05:26.427 --> 05:27.961
- AW, SHIT!

05:27.995 --> 05:29.730
- LANGUAGE.

05:29.763 --> 05:31.064
YOU WANT TO TURN OUR GUS
INTO A TRASH-MOUTH?

05:31.098 --> 05:32.733
- LIKE MOMMY, LIKE SON.

05:32.766 --> 05:35.035
- [chuckles]
- MMMM.

05:35.068 --> 05:37.104
LEDA SAYS WE'RE LOOKING
AT SOME MAJOR REPAIRS.

05:37.137 --> 05:38.972
- OH, NO.

05:39.006 --> 05:41.108
JUST WHEN WE ALMOST HAD ENOUGH
SAVED FOR THE WEDDING.

05:41.141 --> 05:43.444
- GUESS WE'LL JUST
HAVE TO CUT A FEW CORNERS,

05:43.477 --> 05:45.713
LIKE PRINTING UP OUR OWN
INVITATIONS ON THE COMPUTER.

05:45.746 --> 05:47.781
- I AM NOT HAVING
SOME TACKY ANNOUNCEMENTS.

05:47.815 --> 05:49.983
- FINE. WE CAN WALK
TO THE CEREMONY.

05:50.017 --> 05:51.719
- THERE MUST
BE SOME OTHER WAY.

05:51.752 --> 05:52.786
- FORGET MY MOM.

05:52.820 --> 05:56.824
THE EARLY-BIRD SPECIAL
WAS HATCHED IN HER HONOR.

05:56.857 --> 05:58.426
- WHAT ABOUT YOUR FOLKS?

05:58.459 --> 06:00.561
- HUH!
- WHAT, "HUH"?

06:00.594 --> 06:02.796
- HONEY, YOU'RE A DYKE,
YOU'RE MARRYING A JEW,

06:02.830 --> 06:04.097
AND YOU'RE
A REGISTERED DEMOCRAT.

06:04.131 --> 06:05.466
NEED I SAY MORE?

06:05.499 --> 06:06.734
- I'LL BRING IT UP
AT DINNER TONIGHT.

06:06.767 --> 06:07.935
- I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T
WANT TO GO.

06:07.968 --> 06:10.638
- NOW WE HAVE
A REASON TO.

06:10.671 --> 06:11.939
- I DON'T WANT YOU
BEGGING THEM FOR MONEY.

06:11.972 --> 06:12.940
- I'M NOT BEGGING.

06:12.973 --> 06:14.808
THEY PAID FOR ALL THREE
OF MY SISTER'S WEDDINGS,

06:14.842 --> 06:16.510
SO THEY CAN FUCKING WELL
CHIP IN FOR OURS.

06:16.544 --> 06:20.013
- LANGUAGE.
- OOH!

06:20.047 --> 06:21.915
- SO ANYONE UP
FOR BABYLON TONIGHT?

06:21.949 --> 06:24.952
- I CAN'T.
I GOTTA DO INVENTORY.

06:24.985 --> 06:27.588
- I THOUGHT INVENTORY
WAS THE LAST WEEK OF THE MONTH.

06:27.621 --> 06:29.423
- IT IS WHEN YOU HAVE
A BUSINESS THAT'S ON ITS FEET.

06:29.457 --> 06:30.858
BUT, YOU KNOW, WHEN
YOU'RE JUST STARTING OUT--

06:30.891 --> 06:32.793
- ALL RIGHT,
SO WHO IS HE?

06:32.826 --> 06:33.894
- NO--
- WHO IS HE?

06:33.927 --> 06:35.062
- WHO IS HE? WHO IS HE?
- NOBODY. OW!

06:35.095 --> 06:37.931
- I BET IT'S THAT TEACHER.
- [scoffs]

06:37.965 --> 06:39.833
HE'S A PROFESSOR,
NOT A TEACHER.

06:39.867 --> 06:41.669
- OH-HO. THE PROFESSOR.

06:41.702 --> 06:44.638
- SO WHAT DOES THAT MAKE YOU,
MARY ANN OR GINGER?

06:44.672 --> 06:46.173
- SO WHEN DO WE
GET TO MEET HIM?

06:46.206 --> 06:47.441
- NEVER!

06:47.475 --> 06:48.609
- WHY? IS SOMETHING
WRONG WITH HIM?

06:48.642 --> 06:49.743
- SOMETHING WRONG WITH YOU.

06:49.777 --> 06:52.179
I WOULD LIKE THIS ONE TO LIVE,
BEFORE MY BEST FRIENDS

06:52.212 --> 06:54.147
DEVOUR HIM.

06:54.181 --> 06:57.184
- HEY, YOU'RE FETCH DIXON,
AREN'T YOU?

06:57.217 --> 07:00.053
- UH, YES. YEAH.
YES--UH, YES, I AM.

07:00.087 --> 07:01.655
- I'M--
I'M A HUGE FAN.

07:01.689 --> 07:02.956
NOT AS HUGE AS YOU--
- FETCH DIXON!

07:02.990 --> 07:04.625
all: [chuckling]

07:04.658 --> 07:05.793
- [clears throat]

07:05.826 --> 07:08.696
- WHY, THANK YOU.
THAT--THAT'S SO NICE.

07:08.729 --> 07:12.533
- COULD I...SEE IT?
YOU KNOW, JUST FOR A SECOND?

07:12.566 --> 07:14.234
- SHOW HIM.
- ALL RIGHT.

07:14.267 --> 07:16.136
- NO, NO, NO, NO. I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY.

07:16.169 --> 07:17.805
LOOK, IF YOU WANT
TO SAMPLE THE MERCHANDISE,

07:17.838 --> 07:20.240
YOU HAVE TO SIGN ON
TO JERKATWORK.NET.

07:20.273 --> 07:23.744
[whispers]
SORRY.

07:23.777 --> 07:26.614
- THAT'S THE THIRD TIME TODAY.

07:26.647 --> 07:28.616
- WELL, YOU BETTER
GET USED TO IT.

07:28.649 --> 07:29.750
- EMMETT'S A STAR.

07:29.783 --> 07:31.819
- HIS DICK'S A STAR.

07:31.852 --> 07:33.754
HE'S JUST
THE LIFE-SUPPORT SYSTEM.

07:33.787 --> 07:35.088
CAREFUL, HE'LL GET
A SWELLED HEAD.

07:35.122 --> 07:37.691
- HEY, SAVE IT
FOR THE WEBSITE.

07:37.725 --> 07:42.062
- WILL YOU ALL JUST STOP?
I'M NOT A STAR.

07:42.095 --> 07:44.832
I'M STILL LITTLE OLD ME,
YOU KNOW, PLAIN OLD COUNTRY-BOY

07:44.865 --> 07:45.933
FROM MISSISSIPPI.

07:45.966 --> 07:48.869
GIVING MY FRIEND TEDDY
A HELPING HAND.

07:48.902 --> 07:52.640
- [snickering]

07:52.673 --> 07:54.107
- AND THE WAY LYNNETTE'S
BEEN HINTING,

07:54.141 --> 07:56.844
I THINK I MIGHT
BE A GRANDMOTHER SOON.

07:56.877 --> 07:59.246
YOU ALREADY ARE...

07:59.279 --> 08:00.848
IN CASE YOU'VE FORGOTTEN.

08:00.881 --> 08:03.684
- I KNOW, DEAR.

08:03.717 --> 08:06.119
- [sighs]

08:06.153 --> 08:08.822
- THERE YOU ARE.
- MM, THANK YOU.

08:08.856 --> 08:12.059
- UH, MRS. PETERSEN,
THAT NECKLACE IS SO LOVELY.

08:12.092 --> 08:13.861
IS THAT RED CORAL
FROM BALI?

08:13.894 --> 08:15.996
- WHY, YES.
HAVE YOU BEEN?

08:16.029 --> 08:19.900
- NO. NO, ACTUALLY, MY AUNT
DOTTY OWNS A JEWELRY STORE.

08:19.933 --> 08:21.735
- OH.
- LYNNETTE BOUGHT IT FOR ME

08:21.769 --> 08:24.037
ON ONE OF HER HONEYMOONS.
- DON'T ASK WHICH.

08:24.071 --> 08:26.740
- WE DECIDED TO SKIP
OUR HONEYMOON FOR NOW.

08:26.774 --> 08:29.309
YOU KNOW, CONSIDERING
ALL THE EXPENSES?

08:29.342 --> 08:30.944
- WE'RE OUT OF ROLLS.

08:30.978 --> 08:32.312
CAN WE GET SOME ROLLS HERE,
PLEASE?

08:32.345 --> 08:33.446
- OF COURSE.

08:33.480 --> 08:36.116
- WE SHOULD HAVE TRIED
CHEZ DENIS OVER ON THE RIVER.

08:36.149 --> 08:38.318
DUNCAN TOOK LYNNETTE THERE
ON SATURDAY.

08:38.351 --> 08:40.053
HAD A LOVELY MEAL.

08:40.087 --> 08:42.556
- WE'RE THINKING OF HAVING THEM
CATER OUR RECEPTION.

08:42.590 --> 08:43.957
- AREN'T THEY EXPENSIVE?

08:43.991 --> 08:46.093
- WELL, NO MORE THAN
THE ONE LYNNETTE USED...

08:46.126 --> 08:47.561
ALL THREE TIMES.

08:47.595 --> 08:50.330
- YOU GOT TO ADMIT,
SHE'S CONSISTENT.

08:50.363 --> 08:51.899
- AND BESIDES,
GETTING MARRIED THESE DAYS

08:51.932 --> 08:54.768
IS AN EXPENSIVE PROPOSITION,
NO MATTER WHAT YOU DO.

08:59.039 --> 09:02.175
THAT'S WHY WE WERE HOPING
THAT...

09:02.209 --> 09:04.077
YOU MIGHT BE ABLE
TO HELP US OUT A LITTLE.

09:04.111 --> 09:05.178
- IF YOU SEE THE WAITER,
COULD YOU ASK HIM

09:05.212 --> 09:06.747
FOR SOME BUTTER?

09:06.780 --> 09:08.048
- I MEAN, WE'RE HANDLING
IT ALL BY OURSELVES,

09:08.081 --> 09:09.983
BUT WE COULD USE
SOME ASSISTANCE,

09:10.017 --> 09:13.186
NO MATTER HOW SMALL.

09:13.220 --> 09:14.955
ANYTHING WOULD BE HELPFUL.

09:14.988 --> 09:16.156
- HONEY...

09:16.189 --> 09:17.791
- YOU HELPED LYNNETTE
WITH HER WEDDING.

09:17.825 --> 09:20.027
- THAT'S DIFFERENT.

09:20.060 --> 09:22.329
- WHY IS IT DIFFERENT?

09:22.362 --> 09:27.167
- BECAUSE HER WEDDING
WAS REAL.

09:27.200 --> 09:31.639
YOURS IS...

09:31.672 --> 09:34.708
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOURS IS.

09:37.945 --> 09:40.814
HOW'S YOUR STEAK, DEAR?
- JUST GREAT.

09:44.718 --> 09:46.920
- [chuckling]
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME

09:46.954 --> 09:49.122
SINCE I MADE OUT
IN THE PARK.

09:49.156 --> 09:51.725
- WELL, STICK WITH ME,
AND MAYBE YOU'LL GET LUCKY.

09:51.759 --> 09:54.928
- AH, REALLY?
- I FINISHED YOUR BOOK.

09:54.962 --> 09:56.997
- OH, YEAH? SO HOW--
HOW'D YOU LIKE IT?

09:57.030 --> 09:59.232
THE INSECURE WRITER ASKED,
TRYING DESPERATELY

09:59.266 --> 10:01.168
TO SOUND NONCHALANT.

10:01.201 --> 10:04.905
- I DIDN'T. I LOVED IT.

10:04.938 --> 10:07.708
- YOU DIDN'T.
[chuckling]

10:07.741 --> 10:09.242
- ESPECIALLY THAT PART
WHERE THE CUSTOMS OFFICIALS

10:09.276 --> 10:11.979
IN THAILAND CONFISCATED
YOUR HIV MEDS.

10:12.012 --> 10:13.747
- OH, YEAH.

10:13.781 --> 10:16.249
THAT WAS ONE OF THE WORST
DAYS OF MY LIFE.

10:16.283 --> 10:19.386
BUT, AS THEY SAY,
OUT OF ADVERSITY,

10:19.419 --> 10:21.789
YOU KNOW, COMES KNOWLEDGE,
AND...

10:21.822 --> 10:23.223
I'VE LEARNED
TO PUT MY FEARS ASIDE

10:23.256 --> 10:27.127
AND JUST FIND SERENITY
IN THE CHAOS.

10:27.160 --> 10:30.130
- I WISH I COULD DO THAT.
I DO JUST THE OPPOSITE.

10:30.163 --> 10:33.100
I COULD FIND CHAOS IN SERENITY
WITH MY EYES CLOSED.

10:33.133 --> 10:34.301
- [chuckles]

10:34.334 --> 10:37.404
- I THINK THAT THE SECRET
IS TO STOP REGRETTING THE PAST

10:37.437 --> 10:43.410
AND FEARING THE FUTURE,
AND JUST LIVE IN THE NOW.

10:43.443 --> 10:45.879
- SOUNDS LIKE SOMETHING
MY MOM WOULD SAY.

10:45.913 --> 10:48.181
SHE ALWAYS SAYS, "IF YOU'VE
GOT ONE FOOT IN TOMORROW

10:48.215 --> 10:50.784
AND ONE FOOT IN YESTERDAY,
YOU'LL PISS ON TODAY."

10:50.818 --> 10:52.219
- [laugh]

10:52.252 --> 10:54.154
- ACTUALLY SHE SAYS "SHIT"
BUT I WANTED TO CLEAN IT UP

10:54.187 --> 10:55.789
A LITTLE.

10:55.823 --> 10:57.057
- YEAH, ACTUALLY,
YOUR MOM AND BUDDHA

10:57.090 --> 10:58.792
HAVE A LOT IN COMMON.

10:58.826 --> 11:00.894
- WHAT, JENNY CRAIG DROPOUTS?

11:00.928 --> 11:03.263
- NO. NO, UM...

11:03.296 --> 11:04.998
HE TEACHES YOU TO...

11:05.032 --> 11:07.768
FOCUS ON THE SMALLEST DETAILS.

11:07.801 --> 11:11.872
YOU KNOW, THE BREEZE
AGAINST YOUR CHEEK.

11:11.905 --> 11:15.475
THE WAY YOUR SHIRT
FALLS AGAINST YOUR BODY.

11:15.508 --> 11:19.312
THE FEEL OF SOMEONE'S
HAND ON YOUR BACK.

11:19.346 --> 11:24.284
HELPS YOU REALIZE
THAT RIGHT NOW, THIS MOMENT IS--

11:24.317 --> 11:28.388
IT'S ALL THERE IS.

11:28.421 --> 11:31.324
- WELL, IF THAT'S TRUE, THEN...

11:31.358 --> 11:34.361
WE SHOULD PROBABLY
TAKE ADVANTAGE OF IT.

11:34.394 --> 11:37.230
- [whispers]
YEAH.

11:42.135 --> 11:46.006
[overlapping chatter]

11:50.277 --> 11:52.445
